Mandible
(
Figs. 3
F–R; 4A–E; 
7I
). The epipodite is medium-length (
Fig. 3O
), with noticeable verruca and a medium-length seta. The ventral margin of the first endopodite segment (
Fig. 3F
) bears one long seta and two short setae. The disto-dorsal seta on this segment is armed with short spines. The second and third segments are covered with some stiff short spines. The main terminal claw is longer than the basale, but somewhat shorter than the endopodite, and with relatively long thin ventral spines at the middle part. The tooth edge of the coxale is armed with about ten teeth; the distal tooth-list bears 13–16 teeth and the proximal tooth-list has 8–11 teeth. The masticatory pad (
Fig. 4
D–E) has four small rounded flaps, six flat spines and about 25–30 seta-like filaments.
